A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Ego Mang Nwokeka Ndukwe; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Ego Mang Nwokeka Ndukwe is a prominent leader within the broader Nigerian
3 and Igbo-American communities as well as a dedicated community activist; and
4 WHEREAS, she has diligently and conscientiously devoted innumerable hours of her time,
5 talents, and energy toward the betterment of her community and state as evidenced
6 dramatically by her superlative service with several civic organizations; and
7 WHEREAS, she is the Chief Operating Officer of Another Chance Customized Services, a
8 rehabilitation center that supports individuals with disabilities, which she and her late
9 husband founded in Decatur 20 years ago; and
10 WHEREAS, a staunch proponent of inclusivity, she established the American Coalition of
11 Africans with disABILITIES (ECI) in 2001, to advocate for and support individuals with
12 disabilities; and
