13 WHEREAS, she has served as a member of the Governor's Council on Developmental
14 Disabilities, is affiliated with ReBoot Computers for Individuals with Disabilities, and serves
15 with the Friends of Disabled Adults and Children; and
16 WHEREAS, in 2007, she began donating medical equipment to Akahaba Hospital in her
17 hometown of Abiriba, Nigeria, and founded Another Chance Nigeria to empower disabled
18 individuals in Western Nigeria by providing mobility equipment and job skills training; and
19 WHEREAS, her significant organizational and leadership talents, remarkable patience and
20 diplomacy, keen sense of vision, and sensitivity to the needs of both the citizens of this state
21 and around the world have earned her the respect and admiration of her colleagues and
22 associates; and
23 WHEREAS, her life and work exemplify resilience, leadership, compassion, and steadfast
24 faith in God; her legacy continues to uplift and inspire her community; and
25 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
26 remarkable and distinguished community member be appropriately recognized.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body recognize and commend Ego Mang Nwokeka Ndukwe for her
29 efficient, effective, unselfish, and dedicated public service and extend the most sincere best
30 wishes for continued health and happiness.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Ego
33 Mang Nwokeka Ndukwe.
